Preheat your #oven{} to 200℃. Chop the @sweet potatoes{2} into 2cm wide wedges (no
need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a
single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary. Roast on the top shelf
of your oven until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}. Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{30g}. Zest and halve your @lime{1/2}. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse
the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}. Pop half the black beans into a #bowl{} and
mash until broken up, then set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. When the oil is hot,
add the @British beef mince{120%g} and @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and
fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the beef as it
cooks. Once browned, drain and discard any excess fat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Add the @Mexican style spice mix{1} and garlic. Cook for ~{1-2%minutes} then
add the @tomato passata{1}, @BBQ sauce{32g}, @water{100%ml} and the beans (both
whole and mashed). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir and bring to the
boil. Once boiling, reduce the heat and simmer until the sauce is thick,
~{10-12%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook the
> bacon thoroughly.

While your sauce simmers, mix the @soured cream{75%g} with the lime zest and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once the sauce is cooked, taste and season
if necessary.

Once the wedges are done, portion equally into bowls and top with the beef and
bean sauce. Cover with the grated cheese. Finish with a dollop of zesty soured
cream and sliced spring onion. Serve with wedges of lime for squeezing over.
Enjoy!